questionText: Janet Reno was U.S. Attorney General in 1999.
author: A2IU5TX5S0FA1C

questionText: On January 7, 2000 Lazaro Gonzalez filed petition for temporary custody in state court for Elian Gonzales.
author: A2IU5TX5S0FA1C

questionText: Elian's mother drowned when their boat capsized.
author: AJQGWGESKQT4Y

questionText: Elian's mothers dying wish was to keep him in America.
author: A2C84POENS2UNY

questionText: Elian returned to Cuba on June 28, 2000.
author: AJQGWGESKQT4Y

questionText: Elian became a symbol of the continuing struggle between Castro and the US Cuban-exile community.
author: AJQGWGESKQT4Y

questionText: The relatives of Elian Gonzalez challenged the ruling of the INS in court.
author: A1C7UV2UT2S9T7

questionText: Elian Gonzales was rescued at sea on November 25, 1999.
author: A2Q3FS9G8ITCN7

questionText: The courts ruled that Elian should remain in the U.S. until all legal proceedings were completed.
author: A2C84POENS2UNY

questionText: Reno upheld the father's right to custody and ignored Florida court interference.
author: AJQGWGESKQT4Y
